stories.title: West Indies crushed!
stories.summary:
The once champions of the world test and one-day arena crashed out of the
ICC Trophy Tournament in Kenya this past Wednesday as they were heavily
defeated by the mighty Sri Lankan Lions

stories.title: 2nd Match, ICC Knock Out, Sri Lanka v West Indies, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1631st ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Sri Lanka Knock West Indies Out of the ICC Tournament
stories.summary: The hard-hitting opening batsmen Gunawardane scored his first one-day century as the favorites Sri Lanka, batting first, piled up 287 for 6 to beat the West Indies by a margin of 108 runs in the pre-quarterfinal of the ICC KnockOut

stories.title: West Indies head for home as Sri Lanka cruise to victory
stories.summary: It's a long way from the Caribbean to Kenya for just one match

stories.title: Sri Lanka coast to victory
stories.summary:
Sri Lanka established themselves as realistic contenders for the ICC KnockOut
2000 title with a thumping 108-run victory over the West Indies in the second preliminary round match at the Nairobi Gymkhana Club on Wednesday

stories.title: West Indies struggle against Zoyza
stories.summary:
The West Indies seemed to be headed for an early return to the Caribbean as
their top order collapsed against Sri Lanka in the second preliminary match
of the ICC KnockOut 2000 tournament at the Gymkhana Club Ground on
Wednesday

stories.title: Sri Lanka set challenging target
stories.summary:
Aviska Gunawardena rode his luck all the way to a robust century as Sri
Lanka posted a challenging total of 287 for six against the West Indies in
the second preliminary match in the ICC KnockOut 2000 tournament at the
Nairobi Gymkhana Club on

stories.title: Sri Lankan fight back gathers pace
stories.summary:
Aviska Gunawardena and Mahela Jayawardena steadied a wobbly Sri Lankan start
against the West Indian new ball with a confident third-wicket partnership
in the second preliminary round match in the ICC KnockOut 2000 tournament at
the Nairobi Gymkhana

stories.title: West Indies win toss and field
stories.summary: The West Indies won the toss and elected to field against Sri Lanka in the second preliminary round match of the ICC KnockOut 2000 tournament at the Nairobi Gymkhana Club club on Tuesday
